[5] Brazil (Sao Paulo)
Date: Tue 9 Oct 2007
Source: Globo.com [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://g1.globo.com/Noticias/SaoPaulo/0,,MUL146941-5605,00-FORCATAREFA+COMBATE+A+DENGUE+EM+PIRACICABA.html>


The risk of a dengue epidemic in Piracicaba, 162 km (101 mi) from Sao
Paulo, led the prefecture and the Superintendency for Endemic Control
to intensify the fight against the [dengue vector] _Aedes aegypti_
mosquito breeding sites. Action is anticipated in 45 days.

A [vector] control group of 50 agents is in the city now. This Monday
(8 Oct 2007) they will be treating buildings in Vila Cristina, the
neighborhood where most of the 1786 dengue cases have been registered
this year [2007].

--
